title: Which number multiplied by itself is 169? - Quora

response.answer_text: Let us look at this question in a novel manner. Most answers given here are incomplete. The answer is 13 & -13 Proof: Let X be the number when multiplied by itself gives 169 so X^2 = 169 X = 10a+b First Case(if a=0, X=b)------>hence let's go to second caseSecond Case(a=1, X= 10+b)100a^2+20ab+b^2=169=> 100+20b+b^2=169(b+23)(b-3)=0b=-23,3X=-13,13
The number is 13. 13×13=169, 169 is a square of 13. And 13 is a square root of 169.
